I pick up the phone. "Hello?"

"Hello, this is Red Hill Landscaping & Lawn Care calling to inform you that your gardener is under the weather and will be unable to make it today. We apologize for any inconvenience."

"Oh, uh, I think you want my dad. I can give you his--"

"No, I believe we've reached the right person. We'll be in touch. [[Thank you for your patience.]]"

:: Thank you for your patience.

<<audio "rotary-hangup" play>>\
That was weird... I didn't even know we had a gardener. I look out the front window again, but no one's out there except the old lady that lives next door walking her dog. I should get out of here. If that phone rings again, it's gonna startle me.

At least the Advil's kicking in. Maybe I'll draw a comic panel or two. Guess I'll head [[back to my bedroom|Will's Bedroom]].\
